tic\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hgn1665702982492.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hgn1665702982492.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hgn1665702982492.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hgn1665702982492\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Cursor Positioning Mnemonics\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface uses mnemonics to position the cursor.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__section_cgn_jyn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d633985e51\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Mnemonics for Cursor Positioning</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1__entry__1\">Mnemonic </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1__entry__2\">Explanation </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">cursor</code>\n</p>(<var class=\"keyword varname\">h</var>,<var class=\"keyword varname\">v</var>) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1__entry__2\">Position the cursor. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_cursor</code>\n</p>(<var class=\"keyword varname\">h</var>,<var class=\"keyword varname\">v</var>) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hgn1665702982492__table_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1__entry__2\">Position the cursor in graphics mode. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__section_sjr_lyn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d633985e125\">Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__p_d63938e1_d63939e1_d63940e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">%h</var> and\n        <var class=\"keyword varname\">%v</var>—parameters in the output string for this mnemonic indicate the\n        horizontal and vertical position where Uniface wants to position the cursor.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__section_k5p_nyn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d633985e139\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__p_d63944e1_d63945e1_d63946e1\">A definition for <code class=\"ph codeph\">cursor</code> is required for\n        display device tables and is not applicable for printers.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__section_ryb_zyn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d633985e151\">Example: Examples</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__p_d63950e1_d63951e1_d63952e1\">The parameters <var class=\"keyword varname\">h</var> and\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">v</var> specify the coordinates of the home position, for example,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">cursor(1,1)</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">_cursor(6,1)</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__pre_dpz_zyn_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^027[%v;%hH ^CURSOR(1,1)\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__p_d63953e1_d63954e1_d63955e1\">For graphics mode, the coordinates of the position are\n        computed, based on the [<var class=\"keyword varname\">w</var>,<var class=\"keyword varname\">d</var>] values of the current\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">mode_</code> definition, that is, <var class=\"keyword varname\">h</var> times\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">w</var> and <var class=\"keyword varname\">v</var> times <var class=\"keyword varname\">d</var>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"hgn1665702982492__pre_fpz_zyn_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">’P[%h,%v]T’ ^_CURSOR(0,0)\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nsv1665702982422.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Graphics Mode Mnemonics</a><p>The graphics mode set and rest mnemonics in the graphics mode for displays that support them graphics mode.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mzr1665702983304.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Parameters in the Output Sequence</a><p>Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Cursor Positioning Mnemonics Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Cursor Positioning Mnemonics Uniface uses mnemonics to position the cursor. Arguments Table 1. Mnemonics for Cursor Positioning Mnemonic Explanation cursor ( h , v ) Position the cursor. _cursor ( h , v ) Position the cursor in graphics mode. Parameters %h and %v —parameters in the output string for this mnemonic indicate the horizontal and vertical position where Uniface wants to position the cursor. Description A definition for cursor is required for display device tables and is not applicable for printers. Example: Examples The parameters h and v specify the coordinates of the home position, for example, cursor(1,1) or _cursor(6,1) . ^027[%v;%hH ^CURSOR(1,1) Copy For graphics mode, the coordinates of the position are computed, based on the [ w , d ] values of the current mode_ definition, that is, h times w and v times d . ’P[%h,%v]T’ ^_CURSOR(0,0) Copy Related Links Graphics Mode Mnemonics The graphics mode set and rest mnemonics in the graphics mode for displays that support them graphics mode. Parameters in the Output Sequence Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}